## 2. Overview

The Translation Workspace is the primary working area of ATA. All
translation activities begin and end here.

## 3. Goal

-   Minimize user actions
-   Keep source and recommendation visible simultaneously
-   Build reusable translation knowledge
-   Support professional localization workflows

## 4. Scope

### Included (V1)

-   Mode Selection
-   Source Text Editor
-   AI Recommendation Panel
-   Editable Recommendation
-   OCR Entry
-   Sentence Cards
-   Assets Recommendation
-   Workspace History
-   Copy Result

### Out of Scope (V1)

-   AI Chat
-   Compare View
-   Multi Workspace
-   Drag & Drop Files
-   Team Collaboration

### Future (V2)

-   Split View
-   Multiple Recommendations
-   Recommendation Comparison
-   Workspace Snapshot

## 5. UI Layout

``` text
Header
Mode Selection
Source Text | AI Recommendation
Sentence Cards (Conditional)
Assets Recommendation (Conditional)
Workspace History (Conditional)
```

## 6. Components

-   Mode Selection: Required
-   Source Text Editor: Textarea, max 5000 chars
-   AI Recommendation: Editable
-   Sentence Cards: Conditional
-   Assets Recommendation: Conditional
-   Workspace History: Conditional

## 7. Component Behavior

-   Mode is mandatory.
-   Source input enables generation.
-   Recommendation remains editable.

## 8. User Flow

Open → Select Mode → Input Source/OCR → Review OCR → Generate → Edit →
Assets → Copy → Complete

## 9. State Management

Idle → Mode Selected → Typing → Ready → Generating → Editing → Completed

## 10. Validation Rules

-   Mode required
-   Source required
-   Recommendation required before review

## 11. Error Handling

Handle OCR failure, generation failure, network errors and preserve user
input.

## 12. Empty State

Source: Enter source text... Recommendation: AI recommendation will
appear here.

## 13. Loading State

Show loading indicator and disable generation while generating.

## 14. Business Rules

-   AI never overwrites user edits.
-   Assets and History are automatic.

## 15. UX Rules

Workflow over buttons. Minimize clicks.

## 16. Related Features

F003, F004, F005, F006, F007, F009, F011

## 17. Acceptance Criteria

-   Given no mode, generation is disabled.
-   Given mode + source, generation is available.
-   Edited recommendation stays in workspace.

## 18. Developer Notes

-   No AI Recommendation button.
-   No Save to Knowledge button.
-   No standalone Review page.
-   Assets and History are automatic.

## 19. QA Checklist

Mode, Source, OCR, Recommendation, Assets, History, Copy, Empty,
Loading.

